cs.LO, cs.FL, cs.DS, cs.PL, cs.LG 

The paper deals with a logic for expressing structural properties of automata with string inputs and outputs in some monoid. This falls under the category of formal languages and automata theory (cs.FL) and logic in computer science (cs.LO). The paper also discusses the complexity of the model-checking problem, which is related to computational complexity theory (cs.DS). Additionally, the paper studies the expressiveness of the logic in terms of classical structural patterns, which is related to programming languages (cs.PL) and machine learning (cs.LG).
